Spain's metal workers, the biggestorganised labour force, broke off talks with employers over1987 wages, union sources said.    The main Socialist and Communist unions rejected an offerfrom the Confemetal employers' organization for a six pct wagerise, one point above the government inflation target for 1987.The metal working industry has 900,000 workers in 60,000factories.    The unions said they were considering a bid to resume talksnext week. REUTER&#3;